ऊर्जयन्तौपमन्यव
ऊर्जयन्त् औपमन्यव
 is mentioned in the Vaṃśa Brāh
maṇa
	1 as a pupil of Bhānumant Aupamanyava. 1) Indische Studien, 4, 372.

ऊर्जयन्ती
ऊर्जयन्ती
 is regarded by Ludwig
	1 in one passage of the 
Rigveda
	2 as the name of a fort, the stronghold of Nārmara. 
The verse is, however, quite unintelligible.
	3 1) Translation of the Rigveda, 3, 152. 2) ii. 13, 8. 3) Sāyaṇa makes Urjayantī a Piśācī; 
