takes it adjectivally. Cf. Oldenberg, 
Ṛgveda-Noten, 1, 199.

ऊर्जव्य
ऊर्जव्य,
 a word occurring only once in the Rigveda,
	1 is 
taken by Ludwig
	2 to be the name of a sacrificer. Roth,
	3 how
ever, regards the word as an adjective meaning ‘rich in strength,’ 
and this is the more probable interpretation. 1) v. 41, 20. 2) Translation of the Rigveda, 3, 155. 3) St. Petersburg Dictionary, s.v.

ऊर्णनाभी
ऊर्ण-नाभी,
 
