ऐरावत,
 ‘son of Irāvant,’ is the patronymic of Dhṛtarāṣṭra, 
as a snake demon,
	1 in the Atharvaveda
	2 and the Pañcaviṃśa 
Brāhmaṇa.
	3 1) In the later literature Airāvata is 
the elephant of Indra: perhaps con
nected with this Vedic snake demon. 
as nāga means both ‘serpent’ and 
