	4 It was not usually kept taut,
	5 but was 
specially tightened when the bow was to be used.
	6 The sound 
of the bowstring (jyā-ghoṣa) is referred to in the Atharvaveda.
	7 
Cf. Ārtnī. 1) iv. 27, 3; vi. 75, 3; x. 51, 6, etc. 2) Av. i. 1, 3; v. 13, 6; vi. 42, 1; 
Vājasaneyi Saṃhitā, xvi. 9; xxix. 51, 
etc. 3) Vājasaneyi Saṃhitā, xxx. 7; Tait
tirīya Brāhmaṇa, iii. 4, 3, 1. 4) Rv. vi. 75, 3; Av. i. 1, 3. In the 
Epic the bowstring is made of hemp 
(maurvī); Hopkins, Journal of the 
American Oriental Society, 13, 271. 5) Av. vi. 42, 1. 6) Rv. x. 166, 3. 7) v. 21, 9. 
