	1 and to be 
the name of a seer in the Rigveda,
	2 presumably a descendant of 
Taku Kakṣīvant, for his name occurs in a group of hymns 
composed by the Kākṣīvatas.
	3 1) Cf. Bhṛgavāṇa, from Bhṛgu; Roth, 
