तण्डुल
तण्डुल,
 ‘grain,’ especially ‘rice grain,’ is mentioned very 
often in the Atharvaveda
	1 and later,
	2 but not in the Rigveda. 
This accords with the fact that rice cultivation seems hardly 
known in the Rigveda.
	3 Husked (karṇa) and unhusked (akarṇa) 
rice is referred to in the Taittirīya Saṃhitā.
	4 1) x. 9, 26; xi. 1, 18; xii. 3, 18. 
29. 30. 2) Maitrāyaṇī Saṃhitā, ii. 6, 6; 
Kāṭhaka Saṃhitā, x. 1, etc.; Aitareya 
Brāhmaṇa, i. 1; Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa, 
i. 1, 4, 3; ii. 5, 3, 4; v. 2, 3, 2; vi. 6, 
1, 8, etc.; śyāmāka-taṇḍula, ‘millet 
grain,’ ibid., x. 6, 3, 2; Chāndogya 
Upaniṣad, iii. 14, 3; apāmārga-taṇḍula, 
