posts,’ in Lāṭyāyana Śrauta Sūtra, 
i. 3, 1; ii. 3, 9.

द्वारप
द्वार-प,
 ‘door-keeper,’ is only found in a metaphorical 
sense in the Aitareya Brāhmaṇa (i. 30), where Viṣṇu is called 
the ‘doorkeeper’ of the gods, and in the Chāndogya Upaniṣad 
(iii. 13, 6).

द्विगत्भार्गव
द्वि-गत् भार्गव
 (‘descendant of Bhṛgu’) is mentioned in 
the Pañcaviṃśa Brāhmaṇa (xiv. 9) as the seer of a Sāman or 
