ologie, 2, 165, n. 4.

परमज्या
परम-ज्या,
 ‘of supreme power,’ is understood by Ludwig
	1 
in one passage of the Rigveda
	2 as the proper name of a great 
man among the Yadus. But it is doubtful whether the word 
is more than an epithet.
	3 1) Translation of the Rigveda, 3, 159. 2) viii. 1, 30. 3) Hopkins, Journal of the American 
Oriental Society, 17, 39.

