the term Puruṣa itself is found earlier
	12 as a measure of length. 
Puruṣa is also applied to denote the length of a man's life, 
a ‘generation’;
	13 the ‘pupil’ in the eye;
	14 and in the gram
matical literature the ‘person’ of the verb.
