 (‘having a speckled leaf’) is the name of a plant 
mentioned in a hymn of the Atharvaveda
	1 as a protection 
against evil beings procuring abortion, called Kaṇvas (pre
sumably a sign of hostility to the Kaṇva family).
	2 It also 
appears in the Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa,
	3 being identified with 
