	5 
thinks that the Glycine debilis is meant. 1) ii. 25, 1 et seq. 2) Cf. Lanman in Whitney's Transla
tion of the Atharvaveda, 65; Bergaigne, 
Religion Védique, 2, 465; Hillebrandt, 
Vedische Mythologie, 1, 207. 3) xiii. 8, 1, 10. 4) Cited by Whitney, loc. cit. 5) xxv. 7, 17. 
Cf. Weber, Indische Studien, 13, 187; 
Zimmer, Altindisches Leben, 69; Bloom
field, Hymns of the Atharvaveda, 302.

