Cf. Zimmer, Altindisches Leben, 154.

प्रोष्ठपद
प्रोष्ठ-पद,
 m., -padā, f. (‘foot of a bench’), is the name 
of a double Nakṣatra.

प्रोष्ठपादवारक्य
प्रोष्ठ-पाद वारक्य
 is mentioned in a Vaṃśa (list of 
teachers) of the Jaiminīya Upaniṣad Brāhmaṇa (iii. 41, 1) as 
a pupil of Kaṃsa Vāraki.

