महानाग
महा-नाग,
 a ‘great snake,’ is mentioned in the Śatapatha 
Brāhmaṇa (xi. 2, 7, 12), where it is plainly mythical.

महानिरष्ट
महा-निरष्ट,
 a ‘great castrated’ ox, is mentioned as the 
Dakṣiṇā, or ‘sacrificial fee,’ in the house of the Sūta at the 
Rājasūya (‘royal consecration’) in the Yajurveda Saṃhitās.
	1 
Cf. Anaḍvāh and Go. 1) Taittirīya Saṃhitā, i. 8, 9, 1; Kāṭhaka Saṃhitā, xv. 4, 9; Maitrāyaṇī 
