of the Aśvamedha (‘horse sacrifice’) in the Yajurveda Saṃhitās.
	1 1) Taittirīya Saṃhitā, vii. 5, 18, 1; Vājasaneyi Saṃhitā, xxii. 22.

महाराज
महा-राज,
 a ‘great king,’ is frequently referred to in the 
Brāhmaṇas.
	1 It seems to mean no more than a king, or rather 
perhaps a reigning and powerful king, as opposed to a mere 
