et seq.; Weber, Indische Studien, 10, 
1 et seq.; Muir, Sanskrit Texts, 1^2, 7 et seq.; 
Ludwig, Translation of the Rigveda, 
3, 242, 243; Hopkins, Journal of the 
American Oriental Society, 13, 76 et seq. 
(for the Epic Vaiśya). 1) x. 90, 12. 2) v. 17. 9. 3) Vājasaneyi Saṃhitā, xxx. 5. etc. 
See Varṇa. 4) Av. vi. 13, 1; Vājasaneyi Saṃhitā, 
xviii. 48, etc. 5) vii. 29. Cf. Muir, Sanskrit Texts, 
1^2, 439. 6) India, Old and New, 222 et seq. 7) Op. cit., 210 et seq. 8) Indian Village Community, 190 et 
seq. 9) Kāṭhaka Saṃhitā, xxxvii. 1. 10) Kauśika Sūtra, lxxx. 11) ii. 5, 4, 4. 12) Rhys Davids, Buddhist India, 55 
