ix. 14, 2 (perhaps an allusion to the 
five tribes); x. 34, 8. 12 (of dice). In 
x. 57, 5, the host of the living (jīva 
vrāta) is referred to. 2) Av. ii. 9, 2 (‘host of the living’); 
Taittirīya Saṃhitā, i. 8, 10, 2; Vāja
saneyi Saṃhitā, xvi. 25; Pañcaviṃśa 
Brāhmaṇa, vi. 9. 24; xvii. 1, 5. 12, etc. 3) v. 53, 11. Cf. iii. 26, 2, where 
